From: damentz <damentz@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] sched: cpufreq_schedutil: use limits_changed for DL boost

Cherry-picked from Liquorix zen/v7.0.12-lqx1.patch (schedutil subset only).
When DL bandwidth exceeds the minimum, flag policy limit changes instead of
forcing an immediate frequency update through need_freq_update.

Signed-off-by: damentz <damentz@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 kernel/sched/cpufreq_schedutil.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/cpufreq_schedutil.c b/kernel/sched/cpufreq_schedutil.c
index 153232dd8276..a8b4c1d2e3f1 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/cpufreq_schedutil.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/cpufreq_schedutil.c
@@ -393,7 +393,7 @@ static inline bool sugov_hold_freq(struct sugov_cpu *sg_cpu) { return false; }
 static inline void ignore_dl_rate_limit(struct sugov_cpu *sg_cpu)
 {
 	if (cpu_bw_dl(cpu_rq(sg_cpu->cpu)) > sg_cpu->bw_min)
-		sg_cpu->sg_policy->need_freq_update = true;
+		sg_cpu->sg_policy->limits_changed = true;
 }
 
 static inline bool sugov_update_single_common(struct sugov_cpu *sg_cpu,
